{
  "answer": "**The *Viṣṇu Smṛti* (Chapter 44) supplies this exact list of stolen items and the corresponding animal rebirths caused by the theft.**[^1]\n\nThe relevant verses (Vi_44.14–29) read as follows:\n\n> A grain-thief becomes a **rat**. // Vi_44.14 //[^2]  \n> A stealer of **bronze** becomes a **swan**. // Vi_44.15 //[^3]  \n> ...  \n> Of **milk**, a **crow**. // Vi_44.18 //[^4]  \n> ...  \n> Of **ghee** [clarified butter], a **mongoose** [ichneumon]. // Vi_44.20 //[^5]  \n> Of **meat**, a **vulture**. // Vi_44.21 //[^6]  \n> ...  \n> Of **salt**, a **cricket**. // Vi_44.24 //[^7]  \n> ...  \n> Stealing **silk**, one becomes a **partridge**. // Vi_44.26 //[^8]  \n> ...  \n> A **cow**, an **iguana**. // Vi_44.29 //[^9]\n\n(A near-identical list appears in the *Manusmṛti* 12.62–64, but the *Viṣṇu Smṛti* matches the query's phrasing and sequence most precisely.[^10])\n\n[^1]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Chapter 44](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/44/translation/).\n\n[^2]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Vi_44.14](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/44/translation/#p-10f0fc).\n\n[^3]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Vi_44.15](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/44/translation/#p-3e2aab).\n\n[^4]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Vi_44.18](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/44/translation/#p-a135b8).\n\n[^5]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Vi_44.20](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/44/translation/#p-0bb922).\n\n[^6]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Vi_44.21](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/44/translation/#p-6e9baf).\n\n[^7]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Vi_44.24](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/44/translation/#p-70946b).\n\n[^8]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Vi_44.26](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/44/translation/#p-6d177e).\n\n[^9]: *Viṣṇu Smṛti*, [Vi_44.29](/works/unknown-visnu-smrti-27f0d8/44/translation/#p-079180).\n\n[^10]: *Manusmṛti*, [Chapter 12](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/12/translation/#p-074f6e).",
